article.description: Elijah Brown scored 25 points, including 14 of New Mexico's final 16 points, to send the Lobos to a 78-73 victory over Boise State on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Brown helps New Mexico hold off Boise State's late rally
article.linkText: Brown helps New Mexico hold off Boise State's late rally
article.story: ALBUQUERQUE, N.M. -- Elijah Brown scored 27 points, including 17 of New Mexico's final 19 points, to send the Lobos to a 78-73 victory over Boise State on Tuesday night. New Mexico (16-10, 9-5 Mountain West) gained control late in the first half on the strength of an 11-0 run during which the Broncos went scoreless for nearly seven minutes. With 19.6 seconds left in the game, Boise State pulled within 76-73 on James Reid's 3-pointer, but Brown finished it off with two from the foul line, where he hit 13 of 14. Chandler Hutchison finished with a career-high 31 points for the Broncos (16-8, 9-4), who never led in the game. New Mexico's all-conference power forward Tim Williams missed his fourth straight game with a foot injury.
